  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a wood-fired oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit",
    "Roll out the flatbread to a thickness of about 1/4 inch",
    "Spread the mashed avocado over the flatbread, leaving a 1/2 inch border around the edges",
    "Top the avocado with crumbly feta cheese, thinly sliced red onion, and chopped fresh parsley",
    "Drizzle the olive oil over the top of the flatbread",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste",
    "Place the flatbread in the wood-fired oven and bake for 12-15 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown",
    "Remove the flatbread from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving"
